<paragraph id="8BE93690FFA2FFA5F8A0FA3BFAC15CDA" blockId="11.[151,1437,1434,1928]" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">Terminalia: Surstyli each with two prensisetae, and a strong, triangular posterior prong (Fig. 3A, 3B). Vesica well developed, broadly rounded but with a clear triangular projection (Fig. 3C). Distiphallus as in Fig. 3D.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE93690FFA2FFA5F8A0FA40FB475F22" blockId="11.[151,1437,1434,1928]" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">
<emphasis id="B922EA82FFA2FFA5F8A0FA40FE4E5CFE" bold="true" box="[199,453,1505,1532]" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">Description of female</emphasis>
(Fig. 2B, 2D). Wing length: 
<quantity id="4CAE9B75FFA2FFA5FB62FA40FCD55CFE" box="[773,862,1505,1532]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
. Very similar to male, except for the obvious sexual differences. Abdominal tergites narrowly grey-brown at posterior edge. Oviscape entirely black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34C651BFFA2FFA5F8A0F988FB755F6A" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE93690FFA2FFA5F8A0F988FB755F6A" blockId="11.[151,1437,1434,1928]" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">
<emphasis id="B922EA82FFA2FFA5F8A0F988FEC95F46" bold="true" box="[199,322,1577,1604]" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is immediately distinguished from its congeners by the tomentose and non-shiny scutellum and the wing pattern, with the posterior band entire, without a hyaline indentation posteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34C651BFFA2FFA5F8A0F9D3FC145FB2" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE93690FFA2FFA5F8A0F9D3FC145FB2" blockId="11.[151,1437,1434,1928]" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">
<emphasis id="B922EA82FFA2FFA5F8A0F9D3FEC55F8E" bold="true" box="[199,334,1650,1676]" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named in honour of the late Bob van Aartsen, friend and mentor of this species’ author. The specific epithet should be treated as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34C651BFFA2FFA5F8A0F918FEB65E66" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BE93690FFA2FFA5F8A0F918FEB65E66" blockId="11.[151,1437,1434,1928]" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">
<emphasis id="B922EA82FFA2FFA5F8A0F918FEAC5FD6" bold="true" box="[199,295,1721,1748]" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">Biology.</emphasis>
So far, all host plant records for species in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C564D13FFA2FFA5FB2AF91BFC305FD6" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" box="[845,955,1722,1748]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Sphenella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922EA82FFA2FFA5FB2AF91BFC305FD6" box="[845,955,1722,1748]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">Sphenella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group of genera are confined to the plant genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C564D13FFA2FFA5F886F97FFEB35FFA" box="[225,312,1758,1784]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922EA82FFA2FFA5F886F97FFEB35FFA" box="[225,312,1758,1784]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">Senecio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C564D13FFA2FFA5F920F97FFE4E5FFA" baseAuthorityName="White" baseAuthorityYear="1988" box="[327,453,1758,1784]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74B61FFA2FFA5F9BAF97FFD055FFA" author="Freidberg, A." box="[477,654,1758,1784]" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" pagination="551 - 559" refId="ref11697" refString="Freidberg, A. (1987) Orthocanthoides aristae, a remarkable new genus and species of Tephritidae (Diptera) from Mount Kenya. Annals of the Natal Museum, 28 (2), 551 - 559." type="journal article" year="1987">Freidberg 1987</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74B61FFA2FFA5FAFCF97FFC495FFA" author="Freidberg, A. &amp; Kaplan, F." box="[667,962,1758,1784]" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" pagination="51 - 94" refId="ref11737" refString="Freidberg, A. &amp; Kaplan, F. (1992) Revision of the Oedaspidini of the Afrotropical Region (Diptera: Tephritidae: Tephritinae). Annals of the Natal Museum, 33 (1), 51 - 94." type="journal article" year="1992">Freidberg &amp; Kaplan 1992</bibRefCitation>
). As for the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C564D13FFA2FFA5FCFEF97FFF695E1E" authority=", Munro (1939)" authorityName="Munro" authorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Oedosphenella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922EA82FFA2FFA5FCFEF97FFACA5FFA" box="[1177,1345,1758,1784]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">Oedosphenella</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74B61FFA2FFA5FD37F97FFF695E1E" author="Munro, H. K." pageId="11" pageNumber="570" pagination="26 - 46" refId="ref12580" refString="Munro, H. K. (1939) Studies in African Trypetidae, with descriptions of new species. Journal of the Entomological Society of Southern Africa, 1, 26 - 46." type="journal article" year="1939">Munro (1939)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
stated that 
<taxonomicName id="4C564D13FFA2FFA5F90EF8A3FE6D5E1E" box="[361,486,1794,1820]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Oedosphenella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auriella">
<emphasis id="B922EA82FFA2FFA5F90EF8A3FE6D5E1E" box="[361,486,1794,1820]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">O. auriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
develops in spindle-shaped stem galls of 
<taxonomicName id="4C564D13FFA2FFA5FBAFF8A3FB945E1E" box="[968,1055,1794,1820]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922EA82FFA2FFA5FBAFF8A3FB945E1E" box="[968,1055,1794,1820]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">Senecio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74B61FFA2FFA5FCE4F8A3FA9A5E1E" author="Merz, B." box="[1155,1297,1794,1820]" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" pagination="215 - 231" refId="ref12342" refString="Merz, B. (1992) The fruit flies of the Canary Islands (Diptera: Tephritidae). Entomologica Scandinavia, 23, 215 - 231." type="journal article" year="1992">Merz (1992)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName id="4C564D13FFA2FFA5FDE6F8A3FE935E42" authorityName="Macquart. The" authorityYear="1843" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Tephritis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canariensis">
<emphasis id="B922EA82FFA2FFA5FDE6F8A3FE935E42" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">O. canariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from flower heads of 
<taxonomicName id="4C564D13FFA2FFA5FA68F887FD305E42" baseAuthorityName="Merz" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[527,699,1830,1856]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="steetzii">
<emphasis id="B922EA82FFA2FFA5FA68F887FD305E42" box="[527,699,1830,1856]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">Senecio steetzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is therefore believed that 
<taxonomicName id="4C564D13FFA2FFA5FB9DF887FBCD5E42" authority="Penado &amp; Smit &amp; Aguiar &amp; Cravo &amp; Rego &amp; Santos &amp; Boieiro, 2020" authorityName="Penado &amp; Smit &amp; Aguiar &amp; Cravo &amp; Rego &amp; Santos &amp; Boieiro" authorityYear="2020" box="[1018,1094,1830,1856]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Oedosphenella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bob" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B922EA82FFA2FFA5FB9DF887FBCD5E42" box="[1018,1094,1830,1856]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">O. bob</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B922EA82FFA2FFA5FC2AF887FB075E42" bold="true" box="[1101,1164,1830,1856]" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21157F9FFA2FFA5FC2AF887FB075E42" box="[1101,1164,1830,1856]" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
most probably develops in 
<taxonomicName id="4C564D13FFA2FFA5F8D3F8EBFE805E66" box="[180,267,1866,1892]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922EA82FFA2FFA5F8D3F8EBFE805E66" box="[180,267,1866,1892]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">Senecio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
too.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34C651BFFA2FFA5F8A0F8CCFD3C5E8A" box="[199,695,1901,1928]" pageId="11" pageNumber="570" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BE93690FFA2FFA5F8A0F8CCFD3C5E8A" blockId="11.[151,1437,1434,1928]" box="[199,695,1901,1928]" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">
<emphasis id="B922EA82FFA2FFA5F8A0F8CCFEE85E8A" bold="true" box="[199,355,1901,1928]" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">Distribution:</emphasis>
Possibly endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="4992F872FFA2FFA5FA35F8CFFD385E8A" box="[594,691,1902,1928]" country="Portugal" name="Madeira" pageId="11" pageNumber="570">Madeira</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
